pr_review_body:
Hey @rum1887, I noticed that another applicant was working on this in #6798 before you. I think they started on this in #6793 which was already closed when you created this one and than continued their work in #6798. 

I am assuming that there was a misunderstanding and some confusion due to that? In the future, please take care to check if there is any previous work on this, especially by a fellow Outreachy applicant. And if there is, please feel welcome to work together and review each others contributions! There should be enough work for everyone.

@arsh73552, I'm sorry for the situation. It seems like this PR is much farther along. 

@mkcor, @jni how should we handle this situation to be fair for each applicant? Considering that their solutions were quite similar, should we include @arsh73552 as a co-author so that both can record their contribution?

@ambujpawar I've refactored the helpers again. They are quite complicated now, but at least they make your implementation simpler. We can always refactor them to make it easier in the future. PTAL.

> Shall we also include the developers of SimpleCopyPaste transform as well?

Nope. We are only changing the infrastructure here. We only need to bring them in if something about the algorithm is unclear. I haven't reviewed that yet. Will send a review soon.

> Do you know how this will impact cache keys with the argv no longer being deterministic? Iiuc, the local cache `CommandRunner` doesn't know about `bounded.rs` and simply sees the argv has changed.

@Eric-Arellano : The `bounded::CommandRunner` is always configured to be below all cache lookups. This is intended, because cache lookups should always be cheaper than actually running a process, and so aren't throttled/bounded.

It definitely is a bit fidgety though... the composition of `CommandRunner`s is powerful, but important to stack just-so.

I did not review `colorbynone2` so my comment may be off basis but having a listener attached to a data structure this way (given two way binding) feels a bit unfortunate.

There were few things you've considered but did you consider having a module level singleton dispatcher object that you use to subscribe and unsubscribe?

```ts
// dispatcher.ts

type EventKey = string;
const listeners: Map<EventKey, Function> = new Map();

export function addListener(type: string, fn: Function) {
  ...
}

export function dispatch(type: string) {
  ...
}
```

@stepkillah Thanks, but we will also need CI support to handle building and testing that.

Could you have a look around https://github.com/mozilla/DeepSpeech/blob/51e351e895b845e48f64f2ccb84d3bbb2b0d3379/taskcluster/tc-build-utils.sh#L240-L338 as well as https://github.com/mozilla/DeepSpeech/blob/51e351e895b845e48f64f2ccb84d3bbb2b0d3379/taskcluster/tc-netframework-ds-tests.sh https://github.com/mozilla/DeepSpeech/blob/51e351e895b845e48f64f2ccb84d3bbb2b0d3379/taskcluster/test-netframework-win-amd64-opt.yml https://github.com/mozilla/DeepSpeech/blob/51e351e895b845e48f64f2ccb84d3bbb2b0d3379/taskcluster/test-netframework-win-cuda-opt.yml https://github.com/mozilla/DeepSpeech/blob/51e351e895b845e48f64f2ccb84d3bbb2b0d3379/taskcluster/test-netframework-win-ttflite-opt.yml

And the final part that will trigger builds https://github.com/mozilla/DeepSpeech/blob/51e351e895b845e48f64f2ccb84d3bbb2b0d3379/taskcluster/win-build.sh#L50-L54

LGTM. It would be nice to add the test for multiple sub-flows queued though:

```
@workflow.virtual_actor
def Counter:
   def incr(self, n):
       self.n += 1
       if n > 0:
          return self.incr.step(n - 1)
     def get(self):
          return self.n
 
 c = Counter.get_or_create("c1")
 c.incr.run_async(10)
 c.incr.run_async(10)
 assert c.get.run() == 20
 ```

@jimfulton wrote:
> The long term fix will be to stop copying this method.

Is there an issue open to track the long-term fix?

Nit comments. Otherwise, looks good to me. 
I believe @vkhromov has been added in the review primarily for visibility or any review-comments related how spark-infra interacts with k8s?

@vkhromov kindly let us know if we need to get blocked on your review-comments.
